    d.department_name,
    e.employee_id,
    e.first_name,
    e.last_name,
    e.experience
FROM

JOIN
    departments d ON e.department_id = d.department_id

    (
        SELECT
            department_id,
            employee_id,
            @rank := IF(@department_id = department_id, @rank + 1, 1) AS rank,

In passive voice, the subject of the sentence is the object of the action in the active voice sentence, and the object of the sentence becomes the subject. In this case, the subject "Bob" is the one who is performing the action of calling the police, so in passive voice, the police become the subject, and Bob becomes the agent (the one who is causing the action to happen). The verb "called" is changed to the past participle "were called," and a form of the verb "to be" is added to complete the passive voice sentence.
